    <strong>Introduction to Chinook Salmon in Oregon</strong>
</h2>
<p>
    Chinook salmon, also known as King salmon, are the largest and one of the most prized fish in the Pacific Northwest. These powerful migrators are renowned for their size, strength, and rich, flavorful meat. In Oregon, they are a vital part of the ecosystem and a significant contributor to the local fishing economy. Their lifecycle—from ocean to river—draws thousands of anglers each year, especially to areas near Eugene.
</p>
<p>
