</h2>
<p>
    Chinook salmon migrate from the Pacific Ocean into Oregon’s rivers to spawn. Understanding their seasonal journey helps anglers pinpoint the best fishing times and locations.
</p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Spring Chinook:</strong> Enter freshwater earlier (March–June). Typically smaller but prized for their taste.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Fall Chinook:</strong> Arrive from August to October. Larger in size, providing a thrilling catch.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Peak Fishing Windows:</strong> Usually coincide with water flow conditions and temperature shifts.
    </li>
</ul>
<p>
