<h2>
    <strong>Essential Gear and Tackle for Chinook Fishing</strong>
</h2>
<p>
    Targeting Chinook salmon requires heavy-duty, reliable gear. Here’s what local experts recommend:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Rod &amp; Reel:</strong> Medium-heavy rods, 8–10 ft, paired with baitcasting or spinning reels.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Line:</strong> 20–40 lb braided mainline with fluorocarbon leader.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Lures &amp; Baits:</strong> Kwikfish, Spin-N-Glo, cured salmon eggs, and herring are all local favorites.
    </li>
</ul>
<p>
    Pro Tip: Visit Eugene’s tackle shops like <strong>Two Rivers Fly Shop</strong> or <strong>Caddis Fly Angling Shop</strong> for region-specific advice and gear.
