<h2>
    <strong>Local Fishing Techniques and Tips</strong>
</h2>
<p>
    Different rivers and water conditions call for different methods. Here are the most effective techniques for Chinook near Eugene:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Back-Bouncing:</strong> Effective in deeper holes. Ideal for presenting bait near spawning beds.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Plunking:</strong> Great from shore, using heavy weights to keep bait in place.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Trolling:</strong> Best for boat fishing, covering more water to locate active fish.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Drift Fishing:</strong> Allows bait to move naturally with the current—popular on the McKenzie.
    </li>
</ul>
<p>
    Combine techniques with knowledge of river flow and temperature for optimal results.
